he - an HTML entity encoder/decoder

- send token to google to verify

- return the entry to the client and populate the DOM with the submission

12959,"How to run a function after a given time in node.JS?

I am building a hosting server with node.JS and mongoDB.
The server will be used for people to save their files remotely. But I do not want to keep unattended files on the server because it will be a waste of memory on the server.
So there are two things I wish to do :
• Delete Files if not attended for more than 10 days
Is there a way this can be done easily?

,Databases are for storing information. You can run a different thread, or even a `cron` job for doing what you are saying. Is there a particular reason you want this to be run from the database?","Embed Field: How to run a function after a given time in node.JS?
